Package: coconots
Type: Package
Title: Convolution-Closed Models for Count Time Series
Version: 1.0
Date: 2023-3-9
Author: Manuel Huth [aut,cre],
	Robert C. Jung [aut],
	A. R. Tremanye [aut]
Maintainer: Manuel Huth <manuel.huth@yahoo.com>
Description: Useful tools for fitting, validating, and forecasting of practical convolution-closed time series models for low counts are provided. Marginal distributions of the data can be modeled via Poisson and Generalized Poisson innovations. Regression effects can be modelled via time varying innovation rates.
Imports:
    Rcpp,
    forecast,
    numDeriv,
    HMMpa,
    stats,
    ggplot2,
    utils,
    matrixStats,
    JuliaConnectoR
LazyData: true
LinkingTo: Rcpp, StanHeaders (>= 2.21.0), RcppParallel (>= 5.0.1)
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.0.2)
Suggests: 
    covr,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
